Questions:
Which aspect of the THUNDER 2 study involves an experimental procedure?
A) Standard preoperative radiochemotherapy treatment for locally advanced rectal cancer;
B) Use of MRIdian for standard radiation therapy without any modifications;
C) Dose escalation based on MRI images acquired during treatment to target radioresistant disease areas;
D) Routine endoscopic and radiological examinations for treatment monitoring.

Correct answer: C

What is the standard treatment option if you choose not to participate in the THUNDER 2 study?
A) You will receive a higher dose of radiotherapy without MRI guidance; 
B) You will receive a combination of external radiation therapy with concomitant chemotherapy, followed by surgery after 8-10 weeks;
C) You will be given an alternative experimental drug therapy;
D) You will only receive surgical intervention without any preoperative treatment.

Correct answer: B
